  "prompt": "Why was the Pakistan national anthem sung first in the India-Pakistan World Cup match?",
  "response": "The Pakistan national anthem was sung first in the India-Pakistan World Cup match due to the traditional protocol followed in cricket matches, particularly in international tournaments like the ICC Cricket World Cup. Typically, when two teams play, the anthem of the team that is listed first on the schedule is played first. \n\nIn this case, if Pakistan was listed first in the match fixture, their anthem would be sung before India\u2019s. This practice is consistent with the way anthems are typically played before sporting events, and it is not reflective of any political considerations but rather follows the rules established by the tournament organizers. \n\nFor future events or specific instances, factors such as venue arrangements or broadcast timelines might also influence the order of national anthems.",
